When you are working with coordinates, you should always use the normalized coordinates.
The coordinates are normalized to the surface bounds (0.0 = top/left edge, 1.0 = bottom/right edge).
The coordinates can go outside the surface bounds when the gaze is outside the surface bounds,
so the normalized coordinates can be outside the 0.0-1.0 range.